org.knime.core.node.workflow

Class SubNodeContainer

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.knime.core.node.workflow.NodeContainer
      • org.knime.core.node.workflow.SingleNodeContainer
        • org.knime.core.node.workflow.SubNodeContainer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EventListener, NodeContainerParent, NodeContainerStateObservable, NodeContainerTemplate, NodeProgressListener

    public final class SubNodeContainer
extends SingleNodeContainer
implements NodeContainerParent, NodeContainerTemplate
    Implementation of a NodeContainer holding a set of nodes via a WorkflowManager and acting like a NativeNodeContainer to the outside.
    Since:
    2.9
    Author:
    M. Berthold & B. Wiswedel

      • performStateTransitionQUEUED

        boolean performStateTransitionQUEUED()
        Called from NodeContainer.queue(PortObject[]) to set state from marked to queued. It's overwritten in SubNodeContainer to be more ignorant with state checks.
        Overrides:
        performStateTransitionQUEUED in class NodeContainer
        Returns:
        true if the state transition was done and the node can now be executed. False if it was marked but it cannot be executed (coming from InternalNodeContainerState.UNCONFIGURED_MARKEDFOREXEC). The calling code will then clear the mark flags.

        Specified by:
        performStateTransitionPREEXECUTE in class NodeContainer
        Returns:
        whether there was an actual state transition, false if the execution was canceled (cancel checking to be done in synchronized block)
